Nigeria’s ex-finance minister and nominee for the office of the Director-General of the World Trade Organisation, Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala has been elected the DG of the World Trade Organisation (WTO). According to reports monitored on TheCable, she polled 104 votes from 164 member countries to defeat South Korea’s trade minister at the final stage of the race. Dr. Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala is a two time minister of finance, Nigeria and former Managing Director Pperations, World Bank. The officla announcement will be made by 3pm Nigerian time. 